sec.p:
A wavelength-dispersive spectrometer (WDXRF, Rigaku ZSX-100e with Rhodium target X-ray) was used. This instrument was controlled by a Software ZSX computer. The ZSX 100e wavelength-dispersive spectrometer characteristics included


analysis of elements from F to U;



4 kW 70 kV end-window X-ray tube;



microarea mapping down to 0.5 mm;



up to 5 primary beam filters, 10 analyzing crystals and 8 limiting area diaphragms;



optional secondary collimators;



automatic sample changer;



compact design; and



multiwindow, multifunction fundamental parameters software (Dumlupinar et al., 2007).
